body:
Wow, why so offensive against this change guys?

@Micr0Bit I think there are already enough ways you can troll with custom maps... And you already get the "This map contains custom rules. Game experience may change." warning when someone selects such a map, so if you don't want to risk getting trolled, don't play on those maps... I could easily create a map that lets rifle man explode (nuke explosion) when they stay on the same cell or add a script that gives players named `abcdefg30` infinite mammoth paradrops, just as example that trolling is already possible in many ways.

> Either enable by default in some mod, or don't do it.

@chrisforbes what do you mean by that? If I didn't missunderstood it: Since we do we require explicit usecases for fixing bugs/adding features?

---

So, somehow I don't get your points, could you please elaborate a bit more?
